---+ Test your Grid User Certificate

Install the [[Documentation/Release3.InstallOSGClient ][OSG Client Tools]] on a Unix resource to [[ReleaseDocumentation.UserCertificate#TestPGC][test]] your [[Documentation.CertificateWhatIs][Grid User Certificate]] and to access [[Documentation.GlossaryC#DefsComputeElement][compute]] and [[Documentation.GlossaryS#DefsStorageElement][storage]] resources provided by the %LINK_OSG%.

---+ A Word of Advice

Your [[Documentation.CertificateWhatIs][Grid User Certificate]] potentially provides you access to large amounts of [[Documentation/GlossaryC#DefsComputeElement][compute cycles]] and [[Documentation/GlossaryS#DefsStorageElement][storage space]]. Safeguard your Grid User Certificate and associated _password_ with the same care used to protect your Social Security Number or Bank Account Information. *Your responsibilities are detailed in [[Documentation.SecurityUserResponsibilities][User Responsibilities]]*.  Contact the %LINK_GOC_OPEN_TICKET% if you suspect your Grid User Certificate has been compromised!

